This paper deals with the classification of constraint satisfaction problems based on the form of constraints, which is a topic in theoretical computer science. The paper presents an algorithm for solving the problem in polynomial time, which suggests that it may belong to the categories of algorithms (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), logic in computer science (cs.LO), or computational geometry (cs.CG).
